  "prompt": "In Japanese, what is the meaning of \"Kimigayo\"?",
  "response": "\"Kimigayo\" (\u541b\u304c\u4ee3) is the national anthem of Japan. The title translates to \"His Imperial Majesty's Reign\" in English. The lyrics are a wish for the Emperor's long and prosperous reign and were originally a poem from the Heian period (794\u20131185). The current melody was composed in the late 19th century, and \"Kimigayo\" was officially adopted as Japan's national anthem in 1999. The lyrics focus on continuity, stability, and the eternal nature of the Emperor's rule, reflecting traditional Japanese values and reverence for the imperial institution.",
